    <summaries>
      <summary>
        <versionCode>00</versionCode>
        <actionDate>2009-10-07</actionDate>
        <actionDesc>Introduced in House</actionDesc>
        <updateDate>2009-10-24T14:29:14Z</updateDate>
        <text><![CDATA[ <p>Water Efficiency and Conservation Investment Act of 2009 - Amends the Internal Revenue Code to: (1) allow, through 2014, individual taxpayers a tax credit for 50% of the cost, up to $750 per year, of installing qualified water efficiency property in a residence; (2) allow building contractors, through 2014, a $1,500 tax credit for each qualified, new, water efficient home constructed and sold to a homeowner; (3) allow the issuance of tax-exempt water conservation bonds; and (4) exempt prepayments under a qualified electricity supply contract from tax-exempt bond arbitrage rules.</p>]]></text>
      </summary>
    </summaries>
